This package implements time-dependent backmapping (reverse mapping) from
coarse-grained to atomistic resolution in LAMMPS.

The method ramps a per-atom resolution parameter lambda from 0 (pure CG)
to 1 (pure AT) uniformly across the simulation box, gradually restoring
atomistic detail. It implements the method described in:

  Krajniak et al., "Generic Adaptive Resolution Method for Reverse Mapping
  of Polymers from Coarse-Grained to Atomistic Descriptions",
  J. Chem. Theory Comput. 2016, 12, 5549-5562.
  DOI: 10.1021/acs.jctc.6b00595

Components:

  fix backmap           - lambda ramp, CG-AT mapping, COM tracking,
                          CG force distribution
  pair_style backmap    - lambda-weighted non-bonded pair forces
  bond_style backmap/*  - lambda-weighted cross-CG bond forces
  angle_style backmap/* - lambda-weighted cross-CG angle forces

Usage:

  See the examples/ directory and the accompanying Python input generator
  (backmap-prep) for complete workflow examples.

Authors:

  Jakub Krajniak (jkrajniak@gmail.com)
